de.uni_mannheim.informatik.dws.winter.matching.rules

Interface Comparator<RecordType extends Matchable,SchemaElementType extends Matchable>

  • Type Parameters:
    RecordType - the type of records that are compared with this comparator
    SchemaElementType - the type of schema elements that are used in the schema of RecordType
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AggregableMatchingRule, AggregateByFirstRecordRule, AggregateBySecondRecordRule, FilteringMatchingRule, IdentityMatchingRule, LabelComparatorJaccard, LabelComparatorLevenshtein, LinearCombinationMatchingRule, MatchingRule, MaxScoreMatchingRule, RecordComparator, RecordComparatorEqual, RecordComparatorJaccard, RecordComparatorLevenshtein, RecordComparatorOverlapMultipleAttributes, StringComparator, VotingMatchingRule, WekaMatchingRule

    public interface Comparator<RecordType extends Matchable,SchemaElementType extends Matchable>
extends java.io.Serializable
    Interface for all AbstractRecord comparators. A Comparator calculates a similarity value for two given records and an optional correspondence. Implementations can test the values of specific attributes or use the correspondence to determine which values to compare. For an example of a specific attribute comparator, see RecordComparatorJaccard.
    Author:
    Oliver Lehmberg (oli@dwslab.de)
